body:
# Overview:
Firebase is: **"...A powerful API to store and sync data in realtime. ..."**

Show the usage of the "**Firebase**" API, to store data in the cloud. This demo is based in the "quick-start" doc.

## Code:
To setup Firebase ...
```java
@Override
public void onCreate() {
    super.onCreate();
    Firebase.setAndroidContext(this);
    // other setup code
}
```
and to connect to a specific database in Firebase ...
```java
 Firebase myFirebaseRef = new Firebase("https://<your-firebase>.firebaseio.com/");
```
To read data from Firebase ...
```java
 myFirebaseRef.child("message").addValueEventListener(new ValueEventListener() {

  @Override
  public void onDataChange(DataSnapshot snapshot) {
    System.out.println(snapshot.getValue());  //prints "Do you have data? You'll love Firebase."
  }

  @Override public void onCancelled(FirebaseError error) { }

});
```
To write data into Firebase ...
```java
 myFirebaseRef.child("message").setValue("Do you have data? You'll love Firebase.");
```

## References:

   Firebase web site: https://www.firebase.com/

   android sdk (quickstart) : https://www.firebase.com/docs/android/quickstart.html
